[White "1. Mainline: 4... dxc4 5. a4 Bf5 6. e3"]
[Black "Mainline: 4... dxc4 5. a4 Bf5 6. e3 intro"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. a4 Bf5 6. e3
{ This is the old mainline of the Slav. With 6. e3 White simply makes sure that he can recapture the c4-pawn with his bishop. He will castle short and then either try to win the bishop-pair or get in the advance e4  (or ideally, achieve both goals)  . Black for his part tries to remain solid, will usually claim the b4-square with the move ...a5 and eventually try to arrange more exchanges as well as the advance ...e5, opening the center favorably for him.  Tactics for White usually involve a kingside attack, while Black often skirmishes successfully along the d-file and sometimes on the kingside, if White has weakened it with various pawn advances. }
*

