[Black "Mainline: 4... dxc4 5. a4 Bf5 6. Ne5 intro"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 dxc4 5. a4 Bf5 6. Ne5
{ This is the main alternative to 6. e3. White prepares to recapture on c4 with the knight, leaving open what he will do to finish the development of his kingside. He can either go for g3 and Bg2 or  (more ambitiously)  play f3 and e4. This gives White an ideal pawn center early on, but also one that is ripe to being attacked - many miniatures in this game see Black sacrificing a piece on e4 to get an early attack on the white king going. }
*

