1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. e3
{ This is the most common reply to the 4... a6 variation, also known as the Chebanenko Slav. White sets up modestly, simply making sure he can recapture on c4 if Black takes there, while still retaining a lot of flexibility. It is not uncommon to see White develop his c1-bishop to b2 in this variation. }
