[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "9. 4. Qc2 dxc4 5. Qxc4"]
[Black "4. Qc2 dxc4 5. Qxc4: intro"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Qc2
{ This is one of the modern antidotes to the Slav. By developing the queen to c2 White cuts across Black's normal plan of developing the c8-bishop to f5. }
4... dxc4 5. Qxc4
{ Since white retakes with the queen on  c4  , he is likely to develop his f1-bishop to  g2  instead of to  e2  or  d3  . While objectively this opening variation is not better for White than the mainlines are, play often resembles the Catalan defense or the Grunfeld more than the Slav, which may not be to every black player's liking!  Games that start with  4.Qb3  dxc4  5.Qxc4  are also included in this chapter. }
*

