O-O Nd7 16. Nxd7 Bxd7 17. Rfc1 Rfe8 18. Qb3 e5 19. dxe5 Bxe5 20. Bc4
{ This wins material as Black can only defend f7 by interrupting his defense of Be5. }
20... Be6 21. Na4
{ 21.Bxe5?  Bxc4  22.Qxc4  Rxe5  and Black is still in the game. } 21... Qb8
22. Bxe5 Bxc4 23. Rxc4
{ White wins a piece because he can now retake on c4 with the rook. } *

